- 2.0.2 | Mar 02 2026:

  -- New Features --

  [New] CLI version cross-check warns when tlog and tlog_lib.sh versions
      diverge after sourcing
  [New] Advisory warnings when baserun directory is world-writable (library)
      or defaults to /tmp for root users (CLI); non-fatal, directs to
      -b/--baserun
  [New] tlog_journal_read() flock support via TLOG_FLOCK=1; returns exit 4
      on contention
  [New] BATS tests: 67 new tests (196 total)

  -- Bug Fixes --

  [Fix] Rotation pipe fallback: when mktemp fails or decompression write
      fails, fall back to pipe-based decompression instead of silently
      dropping rotated content
  [Fix] Baserun directory validated before processing in tlog_read(),
      tlog_journal_read(), and tlog_advance_cursors()
  [Fix] Validate SCAN_MAX_LINES, SCAN_TIMEOUT, and max_lines arguments;
      non-numeric values default to 0 with stderr warning
  [Fix] --status subcommand: correctly display corrupt cursor state with
      raw content for diagnosis; add exit code note to help text
  [Fix] --reset subcommand: clean up orphaned journal timestamp temp files
      alongside cursor temp files
  [Fix] README: document return codes for journal read functions

  -- Changes --

  [Change] Extract rotation into _tlog_handle_rotation() helper; decompress
      once to temp file
  [Change] Internal code cleanup: consolidate duplicated helpers (journal
      cursor pipeline, numeric regex, size calculation, cursor writes),
      remove CLI/library function collision, add stderr warnings on cursor
      write failures
  [Change] CLI --first-run flag validates value (must be 'skip' or 'full');
      rejects typos with actionable error message
